    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="817"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6176/515a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-09">June 9,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4569. Decision has been reached to hold exploratory rubber talks in London.
                    Industry panel<note n="24" xml:id="d817fn24">For list of members of Rubber
                        Advisory Panel, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        June 10, 1944, p. 544.</note> will be so informed at or prior to meeting <pb
                        facs="0979" n="969" xml:id="pg_969"/> scheduled June 14. Tentative date for
                    London meeting not yet proposed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
